                    <h5 allcaps="">Scene. 8.</h5> 
      <h5>
         <span class="add">St Gothard pass</span>An Alpine Bridge.<span class="supralinear">Devil's Bridge</span>
      </h5>
                    <p>We have now before us a view of the far famed
                        <br>Devil's Bridge. The old bridge, of which
                        <br>you see a portion remaining, was constructed as far
                        <br>back as <span class="date" data-when="1118">eleven hundred and eighteen</span>. The span of the
                        <br>arch in the new bridge is seventy five feet, and
                        <br>its height from the surface of the water to the
                        <br>keystone is about one hundred feet, but as the
                        <br>arch spans a cataract almost vertical in its
                        <br>descent the bridge thus acquires an elevation of two
                        <br>hundred feet ad<span class="sic-corr"/>itional.</p>
